args: Captain Valerio, a messenger has arrived\nfrom the capital! He says it's urgent!
Sir, I regret to inform you, but...
You have nothing to worry about,\nYour Highness. Please, just rest.
I will, but... Can I ask you for one thing...?
Yes... Thank you.\nHee hee... It really is you, Valerio.
When did Her Highness fall ill?
She's been eating poorly for several\nmonths now. When she abruptly\ncollapsed, I sent for the doctor.
Is there any hope she'll recover?
Sadly, no. The doctor says she only\nhas about a month left to live.
Her Highness has been waiting so long\nfor you to return. She can't get out of bed,\nand she is too weak to eat.
I beg you, stay by her side. Do what you\ncan to bring her peace in what little time\nshe has left.
She loved to eat so very much...\nAnd now she cannot eat anything at all.
I was sure that as long as my hand could\ngrip a blade, I could protect anything.\nWhat a fool I was...
...Wait. There is still a chance.\nIf anyone could save her now, it's him!
That's right. Did you need something?
Make something for the princess\nout of this.
I bought a little bit of everything that the\nmarket had for sale. I trust it will be\nsufficient?
Her Highness says that she's hungry.\nShe wants something special to eat.
Are you a doctor or a chef? Stop wasting\ntime and start cooking the princess's\nfavorite food! NOW!
F-fine! I'll make it, but I don't know\nwhat you expect to happen!
*cough* *cough* I'm sorry.\nI don't think I can eat anymore...
You've barely had so much as a taste!\nThis is your favorite, is it not? You're\nalways raving about this vegetable stew!
Yes, it was wonderful.\nBut now... Nothing tastes good to me.
I tried to tell you. She's lost her sense\nof taste. It's one of the symptoms of\nher disease.
That's why she hasn't been eating\nnormally, which has only made her\ncondition worse.
I don't want excuses! DO something!\nYou're supposed to be a chef!
What about cookies? Or sandwiches?\nOr foreign cuisine? Do you expect me\nto believe that you've tried everything?!
There has to be something that she'll eat!\nWith proper nutrition, maybe she could\nstart to recover!
Please. Make her something.\nI'd do it myself if I could, but...\nPlease. Please make her SOMETHING!
You have no idea how much I want to\nsee her beaming face—to watch her\ndelight in the joy of eating once more.
But my cooking...\nIt's not going to make that happen.
Later, on their last day together...
Yes, Your Highness. I'm right here.
Your ribbon? But this is your favorite.
Yes. Which is why...I want you to have it.
I can't take this. I'd much rather see you\nwear it the next time we take one of our\nstrolls about town.
How wonderful that sounds...\nI'd bring home lots of tasty food...
Now I understand how it feels...\nTo truly be hungry...
Then I'll take you somewhere to eat!\nIf it would make you feel better, I'll take\nyou anywhere! Any country on the map!
Thank you, Valerio.\nIf ever we meet again...\nI'd like that.
So that guy who was here earlier—\nI'm guessing he was the castle chef?
What about the war?\nDid Mentzara endure?
After Her Highness passed away,\nand before I could return to battle,\nwe officially surrendered.
Mentzara was annexed by our enemy,\nand the country my soldiers fought and\ndied to protect was no more.
In the end, I protected neither the princess\nnor my homeland. I was nothing more than\na fool unfit to serve as a knight.
So ya stopped fightin' altogether and\nbecame a cook, huh?
Indeed. Back then, it galled me that\nI couldn't make anything to serve to\nHer Highness in her hour of need.
I'm not seeing how this connects\nto you closing the restaurant early.
Listen, Mitsuba, this really ain't the time...
No. As a fellow chef,\nI want to hear his answer!
You call yourself a chef, but your\nattitude today was despicable!
As ambassadors to the world of culinary\narts, it is our duty to make sure every\ncustomer's appetite is sated.

It doesn't matter how much your princess
meant to you. The only people you should
be thinking about now are the ones waiting
with empty plates and rumbling guts!
Mitsuba, geez!\nHave a little tact, girl.
No. Every word she spoke is the truth.\nClosing my restaurant out of anger \nwas foolish and impulsive.
I've not grown at all since I lost her.\nI'm every bit as weak as I was back then.
To this end, I intend to grow ever stronger.\nLike you, Valerio.
I must grow strong—as a chef,\nand as a man.
